{"_id":"8ad994bc-2357-32ee-b0a8-5f82407a4260","authorName":"Ravi D","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"cfbc29faa21359b82704f8b7b26398ab","message":"As of the 2016 / 2017 versions of .NET this is not correct, is it? Per .NET documentation. jsonTask.Result.ToString() will block but only until the async task completes, so the runtil will wake up the calling thread and step 8 (Deadlock) does not occur.","postId":"2012_07_dont-block-on-async-code-abe2d9c7-c3e9-3ed8-827c-021686fa2310","replyTo":"","date":"2017-06-29T16:49:52Z","timestamp":1498754992,"authorUserId":""}